    "attributes": {
        "action": "Bring forward provisions for Business Licences for Security Providers",
        "additional_details": "The event industry, pubs and clubs, are struggling, and without adequate regulation of the industry reputable sole traders/companies are struggling to compete with security providers that do not meet appropriate standards.",
        "background": "Plans to require security providers to have Business Licences are on hold, meaning that while individual workers need a licence, businesses are not regulated. This should change, with all security providers required to have business licences, and substantial fines for breaching relevant conditions.",
